cgtree is a command line tool to show cgroup hierarchy, like tree command, on your Linux box.

Installation

 $ sudo cp cgtree.py /usr/local/bin/cgtree
 $ sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/cgtree

Usage

 $ cgtree
 <root>: 84 procs (47.3h)
   x: 15 procs (18.3m)
   ime: 1 procs (1.1s)
   user: 0 procs (7.7s)
     21352: 3 procs (7.5s)
     21339: 2 procs (0.2s)
   browser: 2 procs (1.5h)
 $ cgtree -o memory
 <root>: 105 procs (928.3MB/13.9MB)
   browser: 2 procs (308.5MB/0.0MB)

cgtree -h for complete options.
